div.p:
"I have been striving, for a long time, to get possession of some pure-bred domestic fowls, and a strain of thoroughbred Suffolk swine. I am satisfied you have got them. Now, I beg you will understand that I am fortunately pecuniarily able to pay for what I seek. I care nothing for prices;


This was the kind of customer I met with occasionally, and whom I always took at his word. The gentleman who "did n't care about price" was always the man after my own heart.
                               but I do desire, and stipulate for, purity of blood. Can you supply me? What are your strains? When did you import it, and how has it been bred?
